<title>ITALY: Italy Treasury seeks to reinstate INA voting cap.</title>
<headline>Italy Treasury seeks to reinstate INA voting cap.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1996-11-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>The Italian Treasury said on Thursday it had presented an amendment to the 1997 budget bill which reinstates a voting rights ceiling for the Treasury in insurance companies.</p>
<p>The amendment applies in particular to insurer INA in which the Treasury still holds a 34 percent stake, and in whose statutes there is a fixed five percent voting rights ceiling.</p>
<p>The ceiling on voting rights for the Treasury was abolished in a decree approved in parliament earlier this week.</p>
<p>However the action provoked much criticism from the market and late on Wednesday the Treasury presented the amendment to the budget law, ready for its passage through the Italian upper house or Senate.</p>
<p>--Milan bureau +39 2 66129507</p>
